parse.title: List of postal codes in Mexico

text.*:
This article needs attention from an expert in Mexico. Please add a reason or a talk parameter to this template to explain the issue with the article. WikiProject Mexico may be able to help recruit an expert. (February 2009)

Postal codes in Mexico are issued by SEPOMEX (Servicio Postal Mexicano). The first 2 digits identify a state (or part thereof); and assignments are done alphabetically by state name, except for codes in the 0xxx-1xxxx range which identify the delegaciones (boroughs) of Mexico City.

This is a dynamic list and may never be able to satisfy particular standards for completeness. You can help by expanding it with reliably sourced entries.
